Rating: 4
We love this soup. Instead of peeling and cutting the squash, I cut it in half, scrape the seeds and strings out, and then roast it cut side down on an oiled baking sheet. When its soft and caramelized, I remove it from the oven and let it cool till I can peel off the skin. It's way more flavorful this way, and also less work. If the squash isn't too sweet (or if I use a different variety of squash), I add some brown sugar at the end, so that the sweetness of the soup contrasts better with the spicy chutney. I also serve it with plain non-fat yogurt or sour cream.

